data.chText: （学校、监狱、私人宅院等基督教徒礼拜用的）小教堂
data.enText: a small building or room used for Christian worship in a school, prison, large private house, etc.
a separate part of a church or cathedral , with its own altar , used for some services and private prayer

data.chText: （基督教某些教派如英国的不从国教派教徒做礼拜的）教堂
data.enText: the word for a church used in some Christian denominations , for example by Nonconformists in Britain

data.chText: 她总是在星期天去教堂做礼拜。
data.enText: She always went to chapel on Sundays.

data.chText: （尤指墓地或火葬场的）葬礼祈祷间，祈祷室
data.enText: a small building or room used for funeral services, especially at a cemetery or crematorium

data.chText: （报馆或印刷所的）工会分会，工会分会会员

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a branch of a trade/labor union in a newspaper office or printing house; the members of the branch

word_means: 工会分会，工会分会会员

means: (学校、监狱、私人宅院等基督教徒礼拜用的)小教堂
(基督教某些教派如英国的不从国教派教徒做礼拜的)教堂
工会分会，工会分会会员

ex.enText: The dome of the church is under repair.

ex.chText: 他们的婚礼是在教堂举行的。
ex.enText: Their wedding took place in a church.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指基督徒敬拜上帝、举行宗教活动和婚丧仪式等的场所。

ex.chText: 那座哥特式大教堂吸引着世界各地的游客。
ex.enText: The Gothic cathedral attracts visitors from all around the world.

ex.chText: 我们在导游陪同下参观了大教堂。
ex.enText: We were given a guided tour of the cathedral.

synonyms.bx: 指主教管控下的某一教区内最大的教堂，即主教堂或总教堂，通常装饰精致、宏伟肃穆。

ex.chText: 他建了一座小教堂作为悼念亡母的圣所。
ex.enText: He built a chapel as a shrine to the memory of his dead mother.

ex.chText: 有两个人蹲在学院小教堂的门口。
ex.enText: Two men were squatting at the door of the college chapel.

synonyms.bx: 指学校、监狱、私人宅院等中供基督教徒做礼拜用的专门场所。

tr: a service conducted in a place of worship that has its own altar
a place of worship that has its own altar

value.def: A chapel is a part of a church which has its own altar and which is used for private prayer.
A chapel is a small church attached to a hospital, school, or prison.

example.ex: We married in the chapel of Charing Cross Hospital in London.
example.tran: 我们是在伦敦查令十字医院的小教堂里结的婚。

value.tran: (附属于医院、学校、监狱的)小教堂

value.def: A chapel is a building used for worship by members of some Christian churches. Chapel refers to the religious services that take place there.

example.ex: On Sundays, the family went three times to chapel.
example.tran: 每到星期天，这家人都会去做3次礼拜。

value.tran: (基督教某些派别的)教堂，宗教仪式
